1
00:00:09,903 --> 00:00:16,871
♪

2
00:00:24,759 --> 00:00:28,593
♪

3
00:00:28,723 --> 00:00:31,096
[VAN] 'Tis my solemn vow
to obey your guidance.

4
00:00:31,386 --> 00:00:32,727
And dedicate my whole being

5
00:00:32,807 --> 00:00:34,479
to walking
the path of the Hero.

6
00:00:34,599 --> 00:00:36,932
♪

7
00:00:37,022 --> 00:00:39,775
For this, the will
of our Lord Demis.

8
00:00:39,895 --> 00:00:41,026
Hey.
[gasps]

9
00:00:43,689 --> 00:00:45,491
-Very good, I've found you.
-Huh.

10
00:00:45,611 --> 00:00:48,614
♪

11
00:00:48,694 --> 00:00:50,746
Ljubo. And a guest?

12
00:00:51,247 --> 00:00:53,789
More than that.
Our newest comrade.

13
00:00:54,040 --> 00:00:55,541
My name is Escarlata.

14
00:00:55,832 --> 00:00:57,123
You may call me Esta.

15
00:00:57,503 --> 00:00:58,504
Esta?

16
00:00:58,664 --> 00:01:00,667
The masked knight
of those heroic tales?

17
00:01:01,007 --> 00:01:03,259
Slayer of Demon-General Altra
of the Water?

18
00:01:03,419 --> 00:01:04,671
You're Lady Esta?

19
00:01:05,171 --> 00:01:06,383
Just Esta.

20
00:01:06,763 --> 00:01:08,465
No need for formalities.

21
00:01:08,965 --> 00:01:11,598
Very well, then.
I am Van of Flamberge.

22
00:01:12,389 --> 00:01:13,600
Just call me Van.

23
00:01:14,311 --> 00:01:16,974
Beg your pardon, but Flamberge?

24
00:01:17,144 --> 00:01:20,187
Yes. The eighth prince
stands as the sole survivor

25
00:01:20,277 --> 00:01:21,569
of the Demon Lord's invasion

26
00:01:21,649 --> 00:01:23,280
against
the Kingdom of Flamberge.

27
00:01:23,611 --> 00:01:25,983
A prince of fallen country
turned Hero.

28
00:01:26,534 --> 00:01:28,696
This can only be the will
of the Almighty.

29
00:01:29,287 --> 00:01:32,450
As our crossing of paths,
guided by Lord Demis,

30
00:01:32,790 --> 00:01:35,333
my team is honored
to have you, Esta.

31
00:01:36,624 --> 00:01:38,336
[ESTA]
The honor is all mine, Van.

32
00:01:39,047 --> 00:01:40,458
Come. Introduce yourself.

33
00:01:42,671 --> 00:01:44,963
[chuckles]
Lavender's the name!

34
00:01:45,303 --> 00:01:47,135
Van's confidant
and close partner,

35
00:01:47,215 --> 00:01:48,257
isn't that right?

36
00:01:48,807 --> 00:01:51,059
With that,
our party is thus complete.

37
00:01:51,180 --> 00:01:54,063
The tale we forge will be
one of triumph and victory

38
00:01:54,143 --> 00:01:55,434
where the Hero prevails.

39
00:03:27,531 --> 00:03:32,416
♪

40
00:03:32,496 --> 00:03:34,458
[GODWIN] Go on now,
I told you where they are,

41
00:03:34,538 --> 00:03:36,540
so can you please
cut me loose, lady?

42
00:03:36,830 --> 00:03:37,922
Why should I?

43
00:03:38,002 --> 00:03:40,925
So I can be without a guide
if your words prove false?

44
00:03:41,335 --> 00:03:43,127
Keep your promises, at least.

45
00:03:43,257 --> 00:03:46,260
[fire crackling]

46
00:03:47,722 --> 00:03:50,094
[YARANDRALA] Is it really true
you know the Champion Rit?

47
00:03:50,685 --> 00:03:52,096
How about the man with her?

48
00:03:52,387 --> 00:03:54,979
[GODWIN] Sure, the three of us
are real close.

49
00:03:56,601 --> 00:03:58,733
If that's the case,
do you mind escorting me

50
00:03:58,813 --> 00:03:59,855
to where they reside?

51
00:03:59,945 --> 00:04:01,276
Yeah, whatever you say.

52
00:04:01,446 --> 00:04:04,359
But before that, how about you
and I have some alone time--

53
00:04:04,650 --> 00:04:05,781
[grunts]

54
00:04:05,901 --> 00:04:08,864
[groaning]

55
00:04:11,787 --> 00:04:13,409
They always said
to mind the booze

56
00:04:13,499 --> 00:04:14,710
and watch out for hot women,

57
00:04:14,790 --> 00:04:17,043
so this is what my butt
gets for doing neither.

58
00:04:17,163 --> 00:04:19,085
Less talking and more walking.

59
00:04:19,165 --> 00:04:20,256
Yes, ma'am.

60
00:04:21,167 --> 00:04:22,418
[growling]

61
00:04:22,548 --> 00:04:23,840
[YARANDRALA]
Good day to you, sir!

62
00:04:24,130 --> 00:04:26,262
We're adventurers,
come to meet old friends.

63
00:04:26,973 --> 00:04:28,595
[MALE GUARD 9A]
Adventurers, eh?

64
00:04:29,346 --> 00:04:30,347
[chuckles]

65
00:04:31,978 --> 00:04:33,350
[growling]

66
00:04:34,181 --> 00:04:36,183
[chuckles]
Come right in!

67
00:04:36,563 --> 00:04:37,564
Thank you.

68
00:04:38,315 --> 00:04:39,436
[chuckles]

69
00:04:40,527 --> 00:04:43,490
[GODWIN] [sighs] Tight security
you got here, Zoltan.

70
00:04:44,942 --> 00:04:45,943
Hold on.

71
00:04:46,494 --> 00:04:53,501
♪

72
00:05:01,049 --> 00:05:02,550
-[chuckles]
-[grass rustling]

73
00:05:04,763 --> 00:05:05,764
Hm.

74
00:05:06,464 --> 00:05:08,637
[bird screeching]

75
00:05:09,137 --> 00:05:10,138
[chuckles]

76
00:05:10,519 --> 00:05:11,680
[RED]
You okay, Ruti?

77
00:05:12,271 --> 00:05:13,272
[RUTI]
Fine!

78
00:05:13,932 --> 00:05:18,817
♪

79
00:05:19,028 --> 00:05:20,279
Someone's chipper.

80
00:05:20,649 --> 00:05:22,982
Yep! This is a first
for me, after all.

81
00:05:23,322 --> 00:05:24,323
[RED]
First?

82
00:05:24,573 --> 00:05:27,116
My prior adventures
have always been for service.

83
00:05:27,697 --> 00:05:29,118
I was the Hero then.

84
00:05:29,409 --> 00:05:31,741
But this is the first time
I've taken a peaceful journey

85
00:05:31,831 --> 00:05:33,833
with my brother as only myself.

86
00:05:34,664 --> 00:05:35,705
Who knew...

87
00:05:35,955 --> 00:05:37,337
a simple hike
through the mountains

88
00:05:37,417 --> 00:05:38,748
could be so joyful.

89
00:05:39,089 --> 00:05:40,090
Ruti.

90
00:05:41,751 --> 00:05:42,753
[chuckles]

91
00:05:43,053 --> 00:05:44,845
[RED] The four of us are headed
to the mountain range

92
00:05:44,965 --> 00:05:46,757
called the
Wall at the World's End.

93
00:05:47,257 --> 00:05:49,600
And unlike our travels
as a Hero's party,

94
00:05:50,180 --> 00:05:52,313
there aren't any battles
in store for us today.

95
00:05:53,684 --> 00:05:55,646
Just a lowkey, quiet trek.

96
00:05:55,726 --> 00:05:57,268
[MOGRIM] What're you
standing around for?

97
00:05:57,478 --> 00:05:58,899
-Hurry up!
-[RED] Okay!

98
00:05:59,020 --> 00:06:00,902
Who votes for a quick break
after this?

99
00:06:01,152 --> 00:06:02,323
-[RIT] Yeah!
-[RUTI] Sure!

100
00:06:02,443 --> 00:06:06,828
♪

101
00:06:07,739 --> 00:06:09,531
-[sighs]
-[MOGRIM] Listen, boy.

102
00:06:09,621 --> 00:06:11,833
You're a mad bunch of kids
to want to hike the Wall

103
00:06:11,913 --> 00:06:14,246
when there's so many others
who wouldn't scale those peaks

104
00:06:14,336 --> 00:06:15,587
if their life depended on it.

105
00:06:15,747 --> 00:06:18,290
Much less
for an engagement ring. [sips]

106
00:06:18,420 --> 00:06:21,093
Whatever it takes to get
my hands on a blue sapphire.

107
00:06:21,543 --> 00:06:22,925
It's the only stone
that matches

108
00:06:23,005 --> 00:06:24,296
the color of Rit's eyes.

109
00:06:24,466 --> 00:06:25,597
[MOGRIM]
Oh-ho?

110
00:06:25,678 --> 00:06:28,010
They're rare stones,
but I'll bet the gem giants

111
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:29,261
probably have a supply.

112
00:06:29,552 --> 00:06:31,474
And I hope that
they might sell me one.

113
00:06:32,014 --> 00:06:34,106
I'll only give
an engagement ring once.

114
00:06:34,267 --> 00:06:35,898
So it has to be perfect.

115
00:06:36,189 --> 00:06:37,190
[giggles]

116
00:06:37,770 --> 00:06:39,442
Do you really mean
all of that, Red?

117
00:06:39,692 --> 00:06:41,154
Yeah, of course, I do!

118
00:06:41,274 --> 00:06:43,696
Save it for the honeymoon,
ya lovebirds.

119
00:06:43,817 --> 00:06:45,528
[RED]
You're one to talk, Mogrim!

120
00:06:45,739 --> 00:06:47,410
You joined us for Mink, right?

121
00:06:47,741 --> 00:06:49,533
Are you already married,
Mogrim?

122
00:06:49,743 --> 00:06:51,665
Guess that news slipped
the old noggin!

123
00:06:52,205 --> 00:06:54,037
My missus is pregnant, y'see.

124
00:06:54,458 --> 00:06:56,210
[gasps]
Wonderful!

125
00:06:56,630 --> 00:06:57,961
Wonderful, indeed!

126
00:06:58,502 --> 00:07:00,884
The good doctor said
it might come down to surgery

127
00:07:00,965 --> 00:07:02,797
and taking the child
out of her belly.

128
00:07:03,047 --> 00:07:04,468
I'd do anything to ensure

129
00:07:04,548 --> 00:07:06,430
my wife is comfortable
for the big day,

130
00:07:06,510 --> 00:07:08,142
but all I'm good at
is hammering

131
00:07:08,222 --> 00:07:10,144
and chipping away
with my tools.

132
00:07:10,264 --> 00:07:12,397
Gave it some thought,
and figured I could carve her

133
00:07:12,477 --> 00:07:13,768
a knife out of earth crystal.

134
00:07:14,309 --> 00:07:16,020
Does it have
special properties?

135
00:07:16,401 --> 00:07:18,563
Its blades are famous
for being so sharp

136
00:07:18,653 --> 00:07:20,355
you don't even realize
you've been cut!

137
00:07:20,565 --> 00:07:22,908
Reckon that should ease
her burden during the delivery.

138
00:07:23,819 --> 00:07:25,660
Earth crystal
is hard to come by.

139
00:07:25,991 --> 00:07:27,282
If we find the gem giants,

140
00:07:27,362 --> 00:07:29,204
then we'll find
our sapphire and crystals.

141
00:07:29,575 --> 00:07:32,327
I'm mighty grateful to you all
for allowing this old dreamer

142
00:07:32,418 --> 00:07:33,539
to tag along with you.

143
00:07:35,251 --> 00:07:37,673
Everyone here is thinking
of someone, I see.

144
00:07:38,874 --> 00:07:40,296
-So am I.
-Huh?

145
00:07:40,716 --> 00:07:42,548
[RUTI] My big brother
has traveled all over,

146
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:45,051
and faced countless dangers
for my sake.

147
00:07:45,381 --> 00:07:47,263
You've been so selfless
and supportive,

148
00:07:47,343 --> 00:07:49,686
and yet I've never once
offered the same to you.

149
00:07:50,477 --> 00:07:51,848
So, now it's my turn.

150
00:07:51,938 --> 00:07:53,850
I'll support you
each step of the way.

151
00:07:54,230 --> 00:07:55,232
Counting on it.

152
00:07:56,483 --> 00:07:57,484
[giggles]

153
00:08:01,608 --> 00:08:03,400
[rustling]

154
00:08:04,401 --> 00:08:05,402
Hang on.

155
00:08:06,453 --> 00:08:08,535
Smells like some goblins
are afoot.

156
00:08:08,746 --> 00:08:11,959
Ambushing unprotected travelers
for food and their valuables.

157
00:08:12,249 --> 00:08:13,961
I would've liked
to avoid fighting,

158
00:08:14,041 --> 00:08:15,333
but so much for that.

159
00:08:15,663 --> 00:08:16,964
-Huh?
-[swords clanging]

160
00:08:17,715 --> 00:08:19,217
[grunts]

161
00:08:19,627 --> 00:08:21,629
[clanging]

162
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:24,172
[screaming]

163
00:08:24,262 --> 00:08:25,724
-[grunts]
-[thuds]

164
00:08:26,264 --> 00:08:27,766
-[slashing]
-[blood splattering]

165
00:08:27,926 --> 00:08:31,019
How's the sword feel, boy?
My finest work, isn't it?

166
00:08:31,309 --> 00:08:32,431
[Mogrim grunts]

167
00:08:33,141 --> 00:08:34,483
-[thumps]
-[blood splattering]

168
00:08:36,815 --> 00:08:38,106
[goblins groaning]

169
00:08:38,357 --> 00:08:39,398
[thumps]

170
00:08:41,530 --> 00:08:42,531
Hm?

171
00:08:43,993 --> 00:08:45,154
[RIT]
That's all of them, right?

172
00:08:45,654 --> 00:08:48,327
[RUTI] From what I can gather,
coast is clear for now.

173
00:08:49,498 --> 00:08:51,410
-[MOGRIM] Hmm.
-[RED] What is it, Mogrim?

174
00:08:52,251 --> 00:08:54,003
It was a long time ago now,

175
00:08:54,083 --> 00:08:56,085
but I'm certain
I crafted this spear.

176
00:08:56,256 --> 00:08:57,257
Did you?

177
00:08:57,507 --> 00:08:59,419
So that means
whoever was the wielder

178
00:08:59,589 --> 00:09:01,051
fell prey to the goblins.

179
00:09:01,841 --> 00:09:02,802
[MOGRIM]
Hm.

180
00:09:02,882 --> 00:09:04,805
[RED] This world
is rife with violence.

181
00:09:05,846 --> 00:09:07,217
There isn't
a single person here

182
00:09:07,307 --> 00:09:08,969
who can live
a life free of battle.

183
00:09:09,970 --> 00:09:12,272
The Almighty Demis
grants a Divine Blessing

184
00:09:12,352 --> 00:09:13,774
to all living things.

185
00:09:15,225 --> 00:09:17,648
And the scales of power
tip in favor towards anyone

186
00:09:17,728 --> 00:09:20,231
who battles and slays someone
who has a Blessing.

187
00:09:22,233 --> 00:09:23,905
-I've been thinking.
-Huh?

188
00:09:24,235 --> 00:09:26,948
I've rejected my old life
of endless fighting.

189
00:09:27,158 --> 00:09:29,160
Was it wrong of me
to turn my back on that?

190
00:09:30,041 --> 00:09:32,333
[RED] Ruti has the most
powerful Blessing of all.

191
00:09:33,124 --> 00:09:34,666
The Blessing of the Hero.

192
00:09:35,377 --> 00:09:36,628
Absolutely not.

193
00:09:37,048 --> 00:09:39,171
Don't ever regret
choosing yourself, Ruti.

194
00:09:39,591 --> 00:09:40,752
Your life is yours.

195
00:09:41,803 --> 00:09:43,635
But...is it?

196
00:09:43,755 --> 00:09:46,598
[electricity crackling]

197
00:09:47,930 --> 00:09:51,143
[RUTI] Is me living my own life
really so wrong?

198
00:09:51,684 --> 00:09:52,605
[SHISANDAN]
Indeed.

199
00:09:52,685 --> 00:09:55,358
You must fulfill your duty
as the world's Hero.

200
00:09:55,608 --> 00:09:57,440
The Almighty and all humanity

201
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:59,772
won't allow the Hero
to lead a peaceful life.

202
00:10:00,613 --> 00:10:03,156
And if the Almighty
won't grant me my own life?

203
00:10:03,326 --> 00:10:06,029
♪

204
00:10:06,449 --> 00:10:08,702
[birds chirping]

205
00:10:09,202 --> 00:10:10,533
[YARANDRALA]
This is their home?

206
00:10:10,874 --> 00:10:12,415
[GODWIN]
Well, shucks, no one's in.

207
00:10:12,666 --> 00:10:14,458
I guess those two
must've skipped work

208
00:10:14,538 --> 00:10:15,749
to sneak out on a date.

209
00:10:15,919 --> 00:10:17,130
[YARANDRALA]
A date to where?

210
00:10:17,461 --> 00:10:18,962
How should I know where?

211
00:10:19,092 --> 00:10:21,385
I held up my end of the deal,
so let me go!

212
00:10:21,595 --> 00:10:22,886
[MALE GUARD 9A]
Hold it right there!

213
00:10:22,967 --> 00:10:24,598
Thought you could slip by me?

214
00:10:24,798 --> 00:10:26,010
[GODWIN]
Do I know you, sir?

215
00:10:26,350 --> 00:10:27,762
Cut the act, Godwin!

216
00:10:27,972 --> 00:10:29,724
Rumor had it you
broke out of prison,

217
00:10:29,804 --> 00:10:31,686
but to have the gall
to waltz back here?

218
00:10:31,806 --> 00:10:32,977
You're mistaken.

219
00:10:33,057 --> 00:10:35,980
This fine gentleman is friends
with Rit and Red, you see.

220
00:10:36,270 --> 00:10:37,482
[MALE GUARD 9A]
Don't make me laugh!

221
00:10:37,562 --> 00:10:38,613
-He's a crook!
-[gasps]

222
00:10:38,693 --> 00:10:40,615
This criminal attacked
our Champion Rit

223
00:10:40,695 --> 00:10:41,946
with the help of demons!

224
00:10:42,117 --> 00:10:43,198
He abducted the child

225
00:10:43,278 --> 00:10:44,869
she and Red took
under their wing!

226
00:10:44,990 --> 00:10:46,281
He's no friend!

227
00:10:46,621 --> 00:10:48,203
-Is that so?
-[Godwin gasps]

228
00:10:48,373 --> 00:10:50,626
[YARANDRALA]
Did you betray him as well?

229
00:10:50,706 --> 00:10:53,248
O-Okay, so, we may have
gotten off to a rocky start,

230
00:10:53,328 --> 00:10:56,001
but never in a million years
would I betray my friends!

231
00:10:56,081 --> 00:10:57,333
[grunting]

232
00:10:57,543 --> 00:10:59,835
[whimpering]

233
00:10:59,925 --> 00:11:01,217
Hear me out, please!

234
00:11:01,387 --> 00:11:03,219
-[grunts]
-[bangs]

235
00:11:03,679 --> 00:11:05,051
Whoa, whoa, time out!

236
00:11:05,141 --> 00:11:07,553
-[screams]
-[thumps]

237
00:11:07,643 --> 00:11:09,435
-[GODWIN] Oh, my hero!
-[grunts]

238
00:11:09,726 --> 00:11:12,518
Good grief. So what have you
gotten yourself into this time?

239
00:11:12,599 --> 00:11:14,100
I'm the victim here, all right?

240
00:11:14,190 --> 00:11:15,732
That scary Yarandrala woman

241
00:11:15,812 --> 00:11:18,234
thinks I'm an enemy
of Red's for whatever reason!

242
00:11:18,855 --> 00:11:20,106
Yarandrala?

243
00:11:24,201 --> 00:11:26,283
Traitors must be
brought to justice.

244
00:11:26,864 --> 00:11:28,996
O great monarch
of the forests of old!

245
00:11:29,206 --> 00:11:30,828
The crown ruler of mana.

246
00:11:31,118 --> 00:11:32,580
Origin of all life!

247
00:11:32,750 --> 00:11:35,172
♪

248
00:11:35,252 --> 00:11:38,255
[rumbling]

249
00:11:40,718 --> 00:11:41,969
[roars]

250
00:11:42,090 --> 00:11:45,133
♪

251
00:11:45,223 --> 00:11:46,224
Huh.

252
00:11:46,384 --> 00:11:48,937
[TISSE] Oh, boy, this escalated
super-fast, yep!

253
00:11:49,227 --> 00:11:50,598
Hey, are you crazy?

254
00:11:50,849 --> 00:11:52,981
What are trying to do,
wipe out the entire town

255
00:11:53,061 --> 00:11:55,233
-with that thing?
-[TISSE] You're not helping!

256
00:11:57,235 --> 00:11:58,236
[Godwin grunts]

257
00:12:01,109 --> 00:12:02,571
If Zoltan is under attack,

258
00:12:02,821 --> 00:12:04,703
it's my responsibility
as an adventurer

259
00:12:04,783 --> 00:12:05,905
to protect my home!

260
00:12:05,995 --> 00:12:06,996
[slashing]

261
00:12:07,116 --> 00:12:10,960
♪

262
00:12:11,040 --> 00:12:12,121
[TISSE]
Keep still.

263
00:12:13,623 --> 00:12:15,124
-[thuds]
-[squeaking]

264
00:12:15,465 --> 00:12:17,627
-[grunts]
-[MISTROM] O polar winds,

265
00:12:17,717 --> 00:12:19,589
O life-stealing chill!

266
00:12:20,089 --> 00:12:21,221
Blizzard!

267
00:12:21,341 --> 00:12:24,054
-[wind whooshing]
-[creaking]

268
00:12:26,596 --> 00:12:28,058
[gasps]
Hm.

269
00:12:28,228 --> 00:12:30,140
About time you showed
your face, Granny,

270
00:12:30,230 --> 00:12:31,481
er, I mean Lady Mistrom!

271
00:12:31,561 --> 00:12:32,733
Someone we can trust?

272
00:12:32,813 --> 00:12:34,484
She used to be Zoltan's mayor.

273
00:12:34,565 --> 00:12:37,107
Even the Guild's brass think
she's something special.

274
00:12:37,277 --> 00:12:39,650
Enough flattery,
I'm a retired old coot.

275
00:12:40,150 --> 00:12:42,863
Look, there's more important
things to worry about.

276
00:12:42,943 --> 00:12:44,865
-[shatters]
-I'll stop her.

277
00:12:44,945 --> 00:12:46,537
Can I count on you
to cover for me?

278
00:12:46,617 --> 00:12:47,698
Yes, of course.

279
00:12:47,788 --> 00:12:48,789
♪

280
00:12:49,871 --> 00:12:51,042
[shattering]

281
00:12:52,293 --> 00:12:53,294
[thumps]

282
00:12:54,546 --> 00:12:55,547
♪

283
00:12:56,878 --> 00:12:57,959
[grunts]

284
00:12:59,301 --> 00:13:00,632
-[grunts]
-[clinks]

285
00:13:00,712 --> 00:13:03,715
[groaning]

286
00:13:06,388 --> 00:13:07,639
Tell me, who are you?

287
00:13:07,769 --> 00:13:09,932
Red and Rit's ally
and close friend.

288
00:13:10,312 --> 00:13:11,393
Do not lie.

289
00:13:11,774 --> 00:13:14,396
Just ask them yourself
if you truly don't believe me.

290
00:13:15,187 --> 00:13:17,570
They left for the Wall at the
World's End this morning.

291
00:13:18,190 --> 00:13:19,191
Hm?

292
00:13:20,192 --> 00:13:21,864
And why take a journey there?

293
00:13:22,235 --> 00:13:24,287
Because Red is searching
for a gemstone

294
00:13:24,367 --> 00:13:26,369
to engrave in the ring
he's giving to Rit.

295
00:13:26,619 --> 00:13:27,620
A ring?
[gasps]

296
00:13:27,951 --> 00:13:29,542
You mean an engagement ring?

297
00:13:29,622 --> 00:13:30,623
I do.

298
00:13:32,625 --> 00:13:33,627
[gasps]

299
00:13:34,918 --> 00:13:37,090
♪

300
00:13:37,170 --> 00:13:38,211
My.

301
00:13:39,052 --> 00:13:41,305
So those two mean
to cement their bond.

302
00:13:41,385 --> 00:13:42,386
Wonderful.

303
00:13:42,466 --> 00:13:45,599
Quit your swooning and fix
this mess before you skip off.

304
00:13:45,679 --> 00:13:50,765
♪

305
00:13:54,398 --> 00:13:56,611
Are you sure
this is a good idea, lad?

306
00:13:56,821 --> 00:13:57,822
What's wrong, Mogrim?

307
00:13:57,902 --> 00:13:59,273
[MOGRIM]
Cute and fuzzy as they are,

308
00:13:59,364 --> 00:14:01,276
zoogs are man-eating monsters!

309
00:14:01,366 --> 00:14:02,697
-Hm?
-[gasps]

310
00:14:02,777 --> 00:14:05,330
True, they can be a handful
and unpredictable at times,

311
00:14:05,410 --> 00:14:06,781
but the four of us are safe.

312
00:14:07,412 --> 00:14:08,833
I'm good friends
with their elder.

313
00:14:09,414 --> 00:14:10,665
I shouldn't be too surprised

314
00:14:10,745 --> 00:14:12,287
you've broken bread
with their leader.

315
00:14:12,788 --> 00:14:14,630
You make friends
with anyone you meet.

316
00:14:15,090 --> 00:14:17,793
These little guys are top-tier
experts about the Wall.

317
00:14:17,883 --> 00:14:19,965
If anyone can find
the gem giants, it's them.

318
00:14:20,295 --> 00:14:23,138
It's been far,
far too long, Red!

319
00:14:23,429 --> 00:14:25,221
It has! How are you, Elder?

320
00:14:25,301 --> 00:14:28,474
I know Zoltan is more than
a hop, skip and jump from here,

321
00:14:28,554 --> 00:14:30,556
but you must stop by
every now and then!

322
00:14:30,686 --> 00:14:32,608
Things have been
a bit hectic on my end.

323
00:14:32,899 --> 00:14:35,652
I-I mean we've had
a hard time getting out.

324
00:14:35,942 --> 00:14:37,814
[MALE ZOOG ELDER 201A]
As husband and wife?

325
00:14:37,944 --> 00:14:38,985
We're engaged.

326
00:14:39,195 --> 00:14:40,276
Soon to be married.

327
00:14:40,567 --> 00:14:42,449
May your future together
and our friendship

328
00:14:42,529 --> 00:14:44,281
continue to thrive
and be blessed.

329
00:14:44,371 --> 00:14:45,452
You're too kind.

330
00:14:45,622 --> 00:14:46,703
Oh, right.

331
00:14:46,823 --> 00:14:48,956
Here's a home-cured ham
as a gift from us.

332
00:14:49,326 --> 00:14:50,417
Oh, splendid!

333
00:14:50,497 --> 00:14:51,708
Even more meat to go around

334
00:14:51,789 --> 00:14:53,921
is most appreciated
indeed, yes!

335
00:14:54,581 --> 00:14:56,794
If only we could understand
business etiquette

336
00:14:56,884 --> 00:14:58,005
to barter with others!

337
00:14:58,335 --> 00:14:59,507
Speaking of which,

338
00:14:59,927 --> 00:15:01,138
we're hoping to do
some business

339
00:15:01,218 --> 00:15:02,470
with the gem giants.

340
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:04,762
You wouldn't happen to know
where their settlement is,

341
00:15:04,842 --> 00:15:05,843
do you, Elder?

342
00:15:05,933 --> 00:15:07,015
[MALE ZOOG ELDER 201A]
Why, yes, I do

343
00:15:07,095 --> 00:15:08,346
and would be happy to help.

344
00:15:08,436 --> 00:15:10,398
But please,
promise to be careful.

345
00:15:11,019 --> 00:15:12,851
Lately the temperament
of those fellows

346
00:15:12,941 --> 00:15:14,312
has been quite unusual.

347
00:15:14,482 --> 00:15:16,945
One could even say
they've become downright angry.

348
00:15:17,315 --> 00:15:18,356
Why is that?

349
00:15:18,487 --> 00:15:19,818
[MALE ZOOG ELDER 201A]
Can't say for sure,

350
00:15:19,908 --> 00:15:22,160
so I'd advise you
and your party to take caution.

351
00:15:22,281 --> 00:15:23,322
-[thudding]
-Got it.

352
00:15:23,452 --> 00:15:24,663
-[crying]
-[all gasp]

353
00:15:24,743 --> 00:15:25,954
What happened?

354
00:15:26,285 --> 00:15:27,866
Poor thing fell from the tree!

355
00:15:28,037 --> 00:15:30,289
Branch snapped right
underneath his tiny feet!

356
00:15:30,539 --> 00:15:32,041
-Hush now, no need to fuss!
-[wailing loudly]

357
00:15:32,211 --> 00:15:33,923
-[RUTI] Need help?
-No, we're quite all right.

358
00:15:34,003 --> 00:15:35,544
There's no need
to fret, my dear!

359
00:15:36,175 --> 00:15:37,797
[ZOOG BOY 201A] Oh, wow!
It doesn't hurt anymore!

360
00:15:37,877 --> 00:15:39,338
-Thanks, miss!
-Something's off

361
00:15:39,429 --> 00:15:40,470
about the trees here.

362
00:15:40,550 --> 00:15:43,222
This trunk feels fragile,
which explains

363
00:15:43,303 --> 00:15:45,435
why the branch snapped
and the trees look frail.

364
00:15:45,555 --> 00:15:46,936
[MALE ZOOG ELDER 201A]
How can you tell?

365
00:15:47,097 --> 00:15:49,099
Because I was listening
to the spirits,

366
00:15:49,229 --> 00:15:51,231
though I can't say
for sure the cause.

367
00:15:51,731 --> 00:15:53,814
Red? Can you make
some fertilizer?

368
00:15:54,104 --> 00:15:55,105
Sure can.

369
00:15:55,195 --> 00:15:57,147
I can cook something
with materials here.

370
00:15:57,738 --> 00:16:00,320
Get to it!
It'll be a temporary solution,

371
00:16:00,571 --> 00:16:02,152
but let's do what we can, okay?

372
00:16:02,533 --> 00:16:03,654
What do you say, Elder?

373
00:16:03,954 --> 00:16:05,156
Of course!

374
00:16:05,246 --> 00:16:07,208
We would be most grateful
for your help!

375
00:16:07,618 --> 00:16:12,543
♪

376
00:16:12,713 --> 00:16:15,256
[snoring]

377
00:16:15,837 --> 00:16:22,844
♪

378
00:16:24,636 --> 00:16:25,677
-[RIT] What's on your mind?
-[gasps]

379
00:16:26,678 --> 00:16:28,480
Oh, Rit. Hey, there.

380
00:16:29,021 --> 00:16:31,273
Any second thoughts
about this whole trip?

381
00:16:31,894 --> 00:16:32,935
[sighs]

382
00:16:33,235 --> 00:16:35,738
No, I was just thinking
about my sister's Blessing.

383
00:16:38,691 --> 00:16:40,032
More specifically, I...

384
00:16:40,533 --> 00:16:42,745
I was thinking about
her New Truth Blessing,

385
00:16:43,075 --> 00:16:45,248
and how it's canceling out
the Hero's Blessing,

386
00:16:45,328 --> 00:16:48,000
which tends to strip
one's will and individuality.

387
00:16:48,251 --> 00:16:50,003
That's something
she always wanted.

388
00:16:50,543 --> 00:16:51,754
The joys of life.

389
00:16:52,045 --> 00:16:54,297
Snatched away from her
when she was so young.

390
00:16:55,048 --> 00:16:56,549
Craving a home-cooked meal.

391
00:16:56,760 --> 00:16:59,593
Even dreams, since she had
no need for food or rest.

392
00:17:00,383 --> 00:17:02,466
I'm beginning to think
New Truth...

393
00:17:03,056 --> 00:17:05,469
isn't something she received
from the Almighty.

394
00:17:06,099 --> 00:17:08,272
What if the Blessing came
from within her,

395
00:17:08,642 --> 00:17:11,435
and I'm just clueless
about why or how it happened?

396
00:17:11,685 --> 00:17:12,686
[RIT]
Red.

397
00:17:12,897 --> 00:17:14,608
It's all still a mystery to me.

398
00:17:14,979 --> 00:17:17,191
But whatever happens,
I'll always choose Ruti's side,

399
00:17:17,281 --> 00:17:18,322
no matter what.

400
00:17:18,532 --> 00:17:19,534
Yeah.

401
00:17:19,944 --> 00:17:21,486
And I'll be right there
with you.

402
00:17:26,080 --> 00:17:27,242
Why did we stop?

403
00:17:27,412 --> 00:17:29,044
Something's amiss
with the plant life

404
00:17:29,124 --> 00:17:30,415
-in the area.
-Huh?

405
00:17:30,495 --> 00:17:32,918
And the farther we travel,
the sicker they become.

406
00:17:33,298 --> 00:17:34,960
Could the land's soil
be tainted?

407
00:17:35,170 --> 00:17:37,633
-You can sense that?
-Indeed.

408
00:17:37,963 --> 00:17:39,214
And I fear the root cause

409
00:17:39,304 --> 00:17:40,806
may be found up
in the mountains.

410
00:17:41,056 --> 00:17:43,178
-Hm.
-Let us rest here for tonight.

411
00:17:43,429 --> 00:17:45,431
We'll set up camp
and restart our journey

412
00:17:45,511 --> 00:17:46,642
come tomorrow morning.

413
00:17:46,972 --> 00:17:47,973
[TISSE]
Understood.

414
00:17:49,395 --> 00:17:50,816
[fire crackling]

415
00:17:50,896 --> 00:17:52,228
-[YARANDRALA] Tell me.
-[TISSE] Hm?

416
00:17:52,979 --> 00:17:55,361
What made you decide
for us to travel together?

417
00:17:55,521 --> 00:17:57,273
It's easier to show you
where to go.

418
00:17:57,824 --> 00:18:00,326
There was no need for you
to come all this way with me.

419
00:18:00,697 --> 00:18:02,529
And there was no reason
for me not to.

420
00:18:03,530 --> 00:18:05,492
To be honest,
I also want to see

421
00:18:05,582 --> 00:18:06,993
the Wall's natural hot spring

422
00:18:07,083 --> 00:18:08,915
that I've heard
so many good things about.

423
00:18:10,377 --> 00:18:11,378
Is that all?

424
00:18:11,999 --> 00:18:13,170
That's pretty much it.

425
00:18:14,461 --> 00:18:15,462
Right.

426
00:18:16,043 --> 00:18:17,965
[TISSE] My guess is
Yarandrala doesn't know

427
00:18:18,045 --> 00:18:19,757
that Ruti is with Red and Rit.

428
00:18:20,097 --> 00:18:22,760
When she learns that Ruti
is no longer the world's Hero,

429
00:18:23,551 --> 00:18:25,052
I wonder how she'll react?

430
00:18:25,433 --> 00:18:27,515
Um, can I ask you something?

431
00:18:28,015 --> 00:18:29,147
[YARANDRALA]
You may.

432
00:18:29,307 --> 00:18:30,478
[TISSE]
How did you end up becoming

433
00:18:30,558 --> 00:18:32,310
one of the Hero's
party members?

434
00:18:32,810 --> 00:18:34,863
You know my association
with the Hero?

435
00:18:35,193 --> 00:18:36,194
I do.

436
00:18:36,614 --> 00:18:38,526
After all, I am friends
with Red and Rit,

437
00:18:38,617 --> 00:18:39,778
and one other person.

438
00:18:40,699 --> 00:18:42,030
Then I'm not mistaken?

439
00:18:42,410 --> 00:18:44,413
The man who goes
by Red is actually...

440
00:18:44,623 --> 00:18:46,535
Gideon. Red is Gideon.

441
00:18:46,955 --> 00:18:48,377
I suspected as much.

442
00:18:48,577 --> 00:18:51,040
Good to get confirmation
after all of this time.

443
00:18:52,001 --> 00:18:54,173
Thank goodness.
You're still alive.

444
00:18:55,334 --> 00:18:57,426
Do you know the reason
why I joined their party?

445
00:18:57,636 --> 00:18:59,138
It's not at all complicated.

446
00:18:59,679 --> 00:19:01,140
My dear friend Gideon
was there,

447
00:19:01,220 --> 00:19:02,722
and so I knew I had to be.

448
00:19:03,012 --> 00:19:04,434
[TISSE]
Nothing more than that?

449
00:19:04,594 --> 00:19:06,015
Indeed. Nothing more.

450
00:19:07,016 --> 00:19:08,688
What other reason
could I possibly need

451
00:19:08,768 --> 00:19:10,520
to lend aid
to a close companion?

452
00:19:11,101 --> 00:19:12,102
[gasps]

453
00:19:12,692 --> 00:19:14,774
[YARANDRALA] Saving the world
is an alluring adventure,

454
00:19:14,855 --> 00:19:16,817
and helping people
who require my services

455
00:19:16,907 --> 00:19:19,069
is a perfectly
charitable cause in itself.

456
00:19:20,030 --> 00:19:21,702
But that wasn't reason
enough to gamble

457
00:19:21,782 --> 00:19:24,074
on defeating the Demon Lord
with a party of six.

458
00:19:24,825 --> 00:19:26,457
That's simply an absurd risk.

459
00:19:27,077 --> 00:19:28,249
Do you think so?

460
00:19:29,039 --> 00:19:30,211
[YARANDRALA]
Of course, I do.

461
00:19:30,331 --> 00:19:33,214
Why intentionally fight with
so few people in your party?

462
00:19:34,045 --> 00:19:36,677
The Hero carries the world
squarely on her shoulders.

463
00:19:36,878 --> 00:19:38,800
If she were to fall,
it would spell certain doom

464
00:19:38,880 --> 00:19:40,131
for those under her protection.

465
00:19:40,592 --> 00:19:42,634
Leaving things up to her
is nonsense.

466
00:19:43,304 --> 00:19:45,807
You're saying the Hero
doesn't need to keep fighting

467
00:19:45,887 --> 00:19:47,889
if her defeat poses
much of a risk?

468
00:19:48,270 --> 00:19:49,271
Ah.

469
00:19:50,192 --> 00:19:51,193
I see now.

470
00:19:51,643 --> 00:19:53,195
-Hm?
-[YARANDRALA] Don't you worry.

471
00:19:53,946 --> 00:19:56,028
Gideon and I are
of the same mind about that,

472
00:19:56,949 --> 00:19:58,570
though I am surprised.

473
00:19:58,701 --> 00:19:59,702
Huh?

474
00:19:59,862 --> 00:20:01,904
♪

475
00:20:02,364 --> 00:20:04,076
Ruti's here, too, isn't she?

476
00:20:14,507 --> 00:20:15,798
-So cold!
-Yeah!

477
00:20:15,919 --> 00:20:17,300
Wanna bring back
the old special?

478
00:20:17,380 --> 00:20:18,381
Sure!

479
00:20:18,722 --> 00:20:19,723
[thuds]

480
00:20:21,054 --> 00:20:22,055
-[MOGRIM] Hm?
-[RIT] Hm?

481
00:20:23,517 --> 00:20:25,308
-[RED] Know what I think?
-Huh?

482
00:20:25,729 --> 00:20:27,431
Live your life
the way you want to.

483
00:20:27,981 --> 00:20:29,273
And if the Almighty
has something

484
00:20:29,353 --> 00:20:30,774
to say about it, screw 'em.

485
00:20:31,185 --> 00:20:32,936
Your big brother
has your back, Ruti.

486
00:20:34,738 --> 00:20:37,241
Funny. You always know
the right things to say.

487
00:20:37,571 --> 00:20:38,993
-[chuckles]
-[TISSE] Milady!

488
00:20:39,073 --> 00:20:40,074
[gasps]

489
00:20:41,996 --> 00:20:43,868
Tisse? Is that you?

490
00:20:46,330 --> 00:20:47,292
[gasps]

491
00:20:47,582 --> 00:20:54,589
♪

492
00:20:55,961 --> 00:20:57,262
[YARANDRALA]
Oh, Gideon!

493
00:20:57,462 --> 00:21:04,470
♪

494
00:21:04,970 --> 00:21:06,141
-[thumps]
-[Owlbear 201A groans]

495
00:21:06,221 --> 00:21:07,222
[thuds]

496
00:21:09,935 --> 00:21:10,936
[groans]

497
00:21:11,026 --> 00:21:12,608
[blood splattering]

498
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:14,400
[LJUBO]
Excellent work, Van.

499
00:21:14,820 --> 00:21:16,192
What did you expect?

500
00:21:16,282 --> 00:21:18,574
Van could kill off a horde
of these ugly monsters

501
00:21:18,654 --> 00:21:19,655
in his sleep!

502
00:21:20,827 --> 00:21:22,869
A shame we couldn't
arrive sooner than we did.

503
00:21:23,620 --> 00:21:25,452
There wouldn't have
been any casualties.

504
00:21:26,373 --> 00:21:27,874
-[VAN] Spare your pity, Esta.
-[gasps]

505
00:21:28,585 --> 00:21:30,997
You have witnessed
fulfillment of the roles

506
00:21:31,087 --> 00:21:32,709
-the Almighty has given.
-[ESTA] What?

507
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:35,672
[VAN] The Blessing this owlbear
was bound to make

508
00:21:35,752 --> 00:21:37,714
is its fate
to attack this person.

509
00:21:38,465 --> 00:21:39,807
And this person, in turn,

510
00:21:39,887 --> 00:21:41,558
was fated to lose
his life to it.

511
00:21:42,099 --> 00:21:45,102
They each had roles to play,
and they played them perfectly.

512
00:21:45,603 --> 00:21:47,975
[ESTA] Is this truly what
you think of that dead man?

513
00:21:48,356 --> 00:21:49,267
Yes.

514
00:21:49,357 --> 00:21:52,110
